verbose_text: The biochemical examination showed that depressed patients had significantly lower levels of albumin (3.7 +/- 0.3 vs. 4.0 +/- 0.4; P < 0.001), C-peptide (10.6 +/- 6.5 vs. 13.6 +/- 10.3; P = 0.044), and ABI (0.96 +/- 0.2 vs. 1.04 +/- 0.2; P = 0.028) compared with the non depressed group.
